From fc465102b1ed10019b23d28c57136dade84e3735 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thomas Arcila <134677+tarcila@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Apr 2025 21:06:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Link with openvdb when needed

The device library pulls in nanovdb/openvdb symbols but upstream only
links openvdb into the scene library, breaking the link when
WITH_CYCLES_NANOVDB/WITH_OPENVDB are enabled. The openvdb dependency
target is an INTERFACE library that is a no-op when WITH_OPENVDB is off,
so it can be linked unconditionally.
---
 cycles/src/device/CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/cycles/src/device/CMakeLists.txt b/cycles/src/device/CMakeLists.txt
index 431ae7a80..c220f28cb 100644
--- a/cycles/src/device/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/cycles/src/device/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -147,4 +147,5 @@ set(LIB
   PUBLIC cycles_util
   PRIVATE bf::dependencies::optional::openimagedenoise
   PRIVATE bf::dependencies::optional::osl
+  PRIVATE bf::dependencies::optional::openvdb
 )
--
2.49.0
